      "description": "Insecure authentication implementation: The custom auth middleware performs a constant-time comparison manually but relies on string slicing and Ordinal comparison. While mostly correct, it lacks protection against timing attacks if the .NET runtime optimizes string comparisons unexpectedly; using CryptographicOperations.FixedTimeEquals is the recommended standard.",
      "severity": "high"
    },
    {
      "location": "Program.cs:115-118",
      "description": "Missing Input Validation: The proxy accepts arbitrary JSON bodies and forwards them. There is no validation on the size of the incoming request body, allowing potential DoS via large payload attacks (e.g., sending GBs of data to be buffered in memory by StreamReader.ReadToEndAsync).",
